<paragraph blockId="2.[151,557,439,466]" box="[151,557,439,466]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,557,439,466]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Fall, 1899" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,557,439,466]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticollis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,557,439,466]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,426,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera recticollis</emphasis>
Fall, 1899
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,510,967]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
This species was described from two specimens, one from Winslow, Arizona, the other from New Mexico, again with no mention of a type. It is a well-defined species, with only one other resembling it closely, 
<taxonomicName authority="Westcott. Like" authorityName="Westcott. Like" authorityYear="1971" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticolloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera recticolloides</emphasis>
Westcott. Like
</taxonomicName>
the previous species, the two buprestid catalogs differ with regards type depository: 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,341,618,643]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2264" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (2008 a) A World Catalogue and Bibliography of the Jewel Beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Uol. 1. Introduction; Fossil Taxa; Schizopodidae; Buprestidae: Julodinae-Chrysochroinae: Poecilonotini. Pensoft Series Faunistica No. 76. Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow, 625 pp." type="book">Bellamy (2008a)</bibRefCitation>
gives “ANSP 8381 USNM 58128” and 
<bibRefCitation box="[800,1027,618,643]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2628" refString="Nelson, G. H., Walters, G. C. Jr., Haines, R. D. &amp; Bellamy, C. L. (2008) A catalog and bibliography of the Buprestoidea of America North of Mexico. The Coleopterists Society Special Publication, No. 4, i - iv + 1 - 274." type="book chapter">
Nelson 
<emphasis box="[887,944,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
listed “MCZC 58128 ANSP 8381.” The latter reference also gave “NM” as the type locality, for which there is no basis because no lectotype designation had been published. To clarify this situation we hereby designate as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall, 1899" authorityName="Fall" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera recticollis</emphasis>
Fall, 1899
</taxonomicName>
the specimen in USNM that is labeled as follows: “Winslow, Ariz., Wickham. [p] // 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall" authorityName="Fall" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticollis">
<emphasis box="[1325,1436,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">recticollis</emphasis>
Fall
</taxonomicName>
, type. [h] // Type No 58128, USNM [p, red] // 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall." authorityName="Fall." box="[765,1090,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticollis">
<emphasis box="[765,1028,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera recticollis</emphasis>
Fall.
</taxonomicName>
[h] // Lectotype 
<taxonomicName authority="Fall" authorityName="Fall" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Acmaeodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Acmaeodera recticollis</emphasis>
Fall
</taxonomicName>
, desig. Westcott &amp; Bílý 2018 [p, red].&quot; The specimen bore a lectotype label placed by W. F. Barr in 1971, but he never published this, and the label will be discarded. The specimen in ANSP from “N. M.” becomes a paralectotype, as designated by us on blue card. That specimen also bears an invalid lectotype label designated, but never published, by W. F. Barr in 1/68 (possibly 1/60), which will be kept on the specimen. The listing of MCZC as the type depository by 
<bibRefCitation box="[407,631,942,967]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2628" refString="Nelson, G. H., Walters, G. C. Jr., Haines, R. D. &amp; Bellamy, C. L. (2008) A catalog and bibliography of the Buprestoidea of America North of Mexico. The Coleopterists Society Special Publication, No. 4, i - iv + 1 - 274." type="book chapter">
Nelson 
<emphasis box="[494,550,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
is in error.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
